144
00:09:36,300 --> 00:09:38,865
Wake up and play with me soon.

145
00:09:39,990 --> 00:09:40,990
Dream.

146
00:09:45,061 --> 00:09:46,072
Wake up.

147
00:09:51,780 --> 00:09:53,316
Are you cold?

148
00:09:53,980 --> 00:09:56,320
I’ll cover you up.

149
00:10:05,890 --> 00:10:07,083
How is Dream doing?

150
00:10:11,350 --> 00:10:12,749
What did Kit tell you?

151
00:10:15,660 --> 00:10:16,850
What about Wiwat?

152
00:10:17,320 --> 00:10:18,581
What did he tell you?

153
00:10:37,700 --> 00:10:39,861
If you go on with your evil method,

154
00:10:40,370 --> 00:10:42,010
I’m going to expose you.

155
00:10:43,320 --> 00:10:45,745
Your daughter will be the first to know.

156
00:10:47,643 --> 00:10:49,640
Have a good day, doc.

157
00:11:08,450 --> 00:11:09,876
You probably already know

158
00:11:10,910 --> 00:11:12,778
what Professor Wiwat did.

159
00:11:18,120 --> 00:11:19,338
And I sure hope

160
00:11:20,780 --> 00:11:22,363
you won’t go down the same path.

161
00:11:24,840 --> 00:11:26,312
What’s your solution, then?

162
00:11:28,690 --> 00:11:30,101
What does Kit propose?

163
00:11:30,900 --> 00:11:31,900
Huh?

164
00:11:33,610 --> 00:11:35,570
What’s a way out that works,

165
00:11:35,590 --> 00:11:37,869
that doesn’t end with Dream lying there like that again?

166
00:11:37,912 --> 00:11:40,465
That doesn’t put a razor in Ozone’s mouth?

167
00:11:41,140 --> 00:11:44,189
If you’re still cluelessly looking like you are now,

168
00:11:44,894 --> 00:11:46,890
don’t you dare expect me not to do anything.

169
00:11:47,054 --> 00:11:48,610
Don’t you care at all

170
00:11:49,040 --> 00:11:51,687
that it was Wiwat who put us here in the first place?

171
00:11:51,716 --> 00:11:53,374
It already happened.

172
00:11:53,410 --> 00:11:55,687
There’s nothing we can do to reverse it.

173
00:11:56,160 --> 00:11:57,287
But now…

174
00:11:57,730 --> 00:11:59,607
He’s helping us.

175
00:12:00,370 --> 00:12:01,898
The only reason he wants to help

176
00:12:01,941 --> 00:12:03,498
is because he did this to us!

177
00:12:03,534 --> 00:12:05,345
What will you have me do?

178
00:12:08,370 --> 00:12:10,865
We have never been able to save a single soul.

179
00:12:10,901 --> 00:12:12,870
But now we know how.

180
00:12:13,110 --> 00:12:15,883
It doesn’t matter who will teach us.

181
00:12:17,240 --> 00:12:18,756
What matters is that

182
00:12:19,470 --> 00:12:20,734
the people you love

183
00:12:22,472 --> 00:12:23,472
don’t die again.

184
00:12:23,910 --> 00:12:25,716
But who else will die?

185
00:12:27,076 --> 00:12:29,066
Which children will have to live the lives we’ve been living.

186
00:12:29,090 --> 00:12:30,749
A dead mom, and then a dead dad,

187
00:12:30,792 --> 00:12:32,352
and then a whole lot of dead relatives.

188
00:12:33,960 --> 00:12:35,876
By the time that child is our age,

189
00:12:36,340 --> 00:12:38,392
five people will have been dead.

190
00:12:41,585 --> 00:12:43,590
And in order to evade Leap Day,

191
00:12:43,912 --> 00:12:45,910
you need two babies.

192
00:12:46,950 --> 00:12:49,061
All in all, there will be 10 dead bodies.

193
00:12:50,330 --> 00:12:51,861
And If I was actually in on this,

194
00:12:53,070 --> 00:12:55,534
that’d make 20 deaths.

195
00:13:01,530 --> 00:13:03,134
So you are okay

196
00:13:05,330 --> 00:13:08,189
with Ozone dying instead of those 20 people?

197
00:13:33,900 --> 00:13:35,432
Dream just woke up.

198
00:13:41,156 --> 00:13:42,156
Dream.

199
00:13:42,540 --> 00:13:43,723
Dream, how are you feeling?

200
00:14:02,870 --> 00:14:05,861
He–He saved you.

201
00:14:06,280 --> 00:14:08,450
How are you feeling?

202
00:14:09,450 --> 00:14:10,676
Are you in pain?

203
00:14:10,952 --> 00:14:13,650
I’m really sorry.

204
00:14:13,920 --> 00:14:15,156
I’m okay.

205
00:14:16,040 --> 00:14:17,694
She’s awake,

206
00:14:18,440 --> 00:14:20,232
but it’s best not to move much.

207
00:14:21,060 --> 00:14:22,450
She still has internal bleeding,

208
00:14:22,472 --> 00:14:23,614
in several places.

209
00:14:23,870 --> 00:14:25,250
Talking is difficult enough.

210
00:14:25,280 --> 00:14:27,854
I suggest a long bed rest at the hospital.

211
00:14:31,850 --> 00:14:33,898
But you don’t have to worry about anything anymore.

212
00:14:34,807 --> 00:14:36,810
We found a way to fix Leap Day.

213
00:14:38,710 --> 00:14:41,527
From now on, you will never have to get hurt again.

214
00:14:49,000 --> 00:14:50,029
Let’s go, Ozone.

215
00:14:54,350 --> 00:14:55,832
Kit is waiting downstairs.

216
00:15:00,230 --> 00:15:01,869
He probably wants to know

217
00:15:02,523 --> 00:15:04,520
if you could talk Night out of it.

218
00:15:07,040 --> 00:15:08,690
He’s not exactly a good person.

219
00:15:09,940 --> 00:15:12,989
You know he wants to use you and Night

220
00:15:13,018 --> 00:15:14,203
to exact revenge on me.

221
00:15:17,330 --> 00:15:18,858
I’m not exactly a good person, either.

222
00:15:20,901 --> 00:15:22,400
You know that already.

223
00:15:25,420 --> 00:15:26,749
But I have a solution

224
00:15:27,400 --> 00:15:28,530
and I’m here to help.

225
00:15:49,950 --> 00:15:51,323
It’s nothing, Dream.

226
00:16:04,530 --> 00:16:06,406
We need to go to your place as soon as possible.

227
00:16:06,430 --> 00:16:07,941
We need to find a solution to Leap Day.

228
00:16:07,963 --> 00:16:09,287
That means Night…

229
00:16:09,720 --> 00:16:11,200
chose to believe that jerk?

230
00:16:15,400 --> 00:16:16,618
For now.

231
00:16:22,440 --> 00:16:24,145
I’m not letting you die.

232
00:16:26,230 --> 00:16:27,883
I won’t trade you for anything.

233
00:16:30,420 --> 00:16:33,025
There has to be a way nobody has to get hurt.

234
00:16:33,750 --> 00:16:35,112
Give me some time, Ozone,

235
00:16:36,250 --> 00:16:37,250
Okay.

236
00:16:38,390 --> 00:16:39,861
I can wait.

237
00:16:42,378 --> 00:16:43,378
Let’s go.

238
00:16:51,780 --> 00:16:54,189
I need at least one nurse here at all times.

239
00:16:55,350 --> 00:16:56,499
Come by to check on her every hour

240
00:16:56,523 --> 00:16:57,665
in case she needs anything.

241
00:16:57,990 --> 00:16:59,796
I will write you a letter of recommendation

242
00:16:59,825 --> 00:17:01,483
once the job is done.

243
00:17:01,770 --> 00:17:03,054
Of course, Professor.

244
00:17:04,840 --> 00:17:06,880
Don’t you act up now.

245
00:17:06,909 --> 00:17:07,990
Just stay still

246
00:17:08,029 --> 00:17:09,214
so you can recover quickly.

247
00:17:14,300 --> 00:17:16,603
Stay with Dream for the week.

248
00:17:17,400 --> 00:17:19,047
We’ll start next week.

249
00:17:20,650 --> 00:17:21,869
Don’t worry.

250
00:17:22,109 --> 00:17:23,323
We have time.

251
00:17:24,350 --> 00:17:27,018
You wouldn’t be able to focus on anything now anyway.

252
00:17:28,490 --> 00:17:30,952
I’ve talked to the doctors and nurses here for you.

253
00:17:35,710 --> 00:17:36,710
Thank you.

254
00:17:49,110 --> 00:17:52,145
Professor Wiwat really has Leap Day, just like we thought.

255
00:17:52,589 --> 00:17:53,883
But he’s cured.

256
00:17:54,470 --> 00:17:55,876
He has a solution.

257
00:17:57,000 --> 00:17:58,509
He will help us.

258
00:18:01,130 --> 00:18:02,930
Don’t worry about a thing, Dream.

259
00:18:02,960 --> 00:18:04,589
Once you’re better,

260
00:18:04,632 --> 00:18:06,276
I’ll tell you everything.

