00:38:40,487 --> 00:38:42,341
Or is she in the dark, even now?

577
00:38:50,970 --> 00:38:51,970
Dream.

578
00:38:54,480 --> 00:38:55,592
What are you doing here?

579
00:38:57,410 --> 00:38:59,672
Will you leave Night alone, Professor?

580
00:39:04,950 --> 00:39:06,647
Dream, stop it.

581
00:39:26,440 --> 00:39:27,440
Night.

582
00:39:30,350 --> 00:39:31,905
Do you want us to stop?

583
00:39:59,430 --> 00:40:00,430
No.

584
00:40:09,190 --> 00:40:09,890
Dream.

585
00:40:09,912 --> 00:40:10,356
Dream.

586
00:40:10,392 --> 00:40:11,745
- Let go.
- Hear me out.

587
00:40:14,520 --> 00:40:15,520
Don’t think.

588
00:40:16,580 --> 00:40:17,672
Don’t falter.

589
00:40:19,992 --> 00:40:21,738
Just know you’re doing this for her.

590
00:40:32,930 --> 00:40:33,930
Coming.

591
00:40:39,910 --> 00:40:40,996
Oh, Dream?

592
00:40:47,160 --> 00:40:48,254
How are you feeling?

593
00:40:53,770 --> 00:40:54,770
Dream!

594
00:41:00,490 --> 00:41:03,221
Why the long face?

595
00:41:09,110 --> 00:41:10,654
I know about Wiwat now.

596
00:41:16,530 --> 00:41:21,338
I think we need to find another solution to Leap Day.

597
00:41:21,760 --> 00:41:23,534
Once we find a way,

598
00:41:23,570 --> 00:41:24,778
Night will…

599
00:41:24,807 --> 00:41:26,232
That’s exactly what I think.

600
00:41:28,230 --> 00:41:30,400
We need to stop Night and Wiwat.

601
00:41:31,590 --> 00:41:32,763
But here’s the thing…

602
00:41:33,941 --> 00:41:35,352
It’s not easy, Dream.

603
00:41:36,100 --> 00:41:38,116
Ever since you got in the accident,

604
00:41:38,152 --> 00:41:40,007
Kit and I…

605
00:41:40,043 --> 00:41:41,250
And Ozone!

606
00:41:43,040 --> 00:41:45,200
…and Ozone have been working to find another solution.

607
00:41:46,567 --> 00:41:50,509
There’s a new drawing by Ozone on Leap Day.

608
00:41:51,130 --> 00:41:52,741
But still, we have no clues,

609
00:41:53,480 --> 00:41:56,814
except for the fact that Kit and Wiwat will likely be there

610
00:41:56,843 --> 00:41:58,600
on the next Leap Day.

611
00:42:02,900 --> 00:42:05,185
Can we go meet Kit?

612
00:42:05,229 --> 00:42:07,898
And will you let me see Ozone’s drawing?

613
00:42:09,825 --> 00:42:12,210
I will grab the drawing.

614
00:42:40,640 --> 00:42:42,792
I’m sorry about you and Night.

615
00:42:53,340 --> 00:42:54,349
I’m sorry.

616
00:42:56,923 --> 00:42:58,920
If I didn’t take Ozone away,

617
00:42:59,658 --> 00:43:02,018
you might not have to go through anything like that at all.

618
00:43:02,341 --> 00:43:03,341
It’s okay.

619
00:43:05,210 --> 00:43:07,890
Nobody ever meant for this to happen.

620
00:43:08,680 --> 00:43:11,549
I think we should focus on finding a solution for Leap Day.

621
00:43:17,360 --> 00:43:20,516
This is everything I have on February 29-born people.

622
00:43:21,440 --> 00:43:23,643
Ozone, why don’t you show him the drawing?

623
00:43:24,210 --> 00:43:25,592
Your drawing.

624
00:43:25,629 --> 00:43:28,065
These are the accidents that happened on the same days.

625
00:43:41,720 --> 00:43:42,669
Here.

626
00:43:42,705 --> 00:43:44,145
Ozone drew these.

627
00:43:44,189 --> 00:43:46,149
I’m sure they have something to do with Leap Day.

628
00:43:57,400 --> 00:43:58,400
Wrong.

629
00:43:59,490 --> 00:44:01,047
Make sure you do it right.

630
00:44:01,076 --> 00:44:02,076
Do it again.

631
00:44:07,540 --> 00:44:08,540
Focus.

632
00:44:11,610 --> 00:44:12,610
Wrong.

633
00:44:13,550 --> 00:44:14,865
Get yourself together, Night.

634
00:44:15,530 --> 00:44:16,530
Yes.

635
00:44:17,250 --> 00:44:18,250
Wrong!

636
00:44:35,600 --> 00:44:36,600
Wrong.

637
00:44:51,160 --> 00:44:52,160
Wrong.

638
00:44:53,950 --> 00:44:54,950
Night.

639
00:44:55,850 --> 00:44:57,156
Pull yourself together.

640
00:45:07,620 --> 00:45:09,418
Night, you’re not here at all.

641
00:45:11,210 --> 00:45:12,938
Make sure you’re more ready tomorrow.

642
00:45:14,940 --> 00:45:15,940
Yes.

643
00:45:16,150 --> 00:45:17,381
That’s it for today.

644
00:45:20,200 --> 00:45:21,200
Oh, hey…

645
00:45:23,790 --> 00:45:24,790
Are you hungry?

646
00:45:27,700 --> 00:45:28,996
Join us for dinner.

647
00:45:31,040 --> 00:45:32,040
Come on.

648
00:45:39,650 --> 00:45:40,650
Oh.

649
00:45:41,270 --> 00:45:42,560
Are you finished, honey?

650
00:45:43,192 --> 00:45:45,190
I made dinner.

651
00:45:45,710 --> 00:45:46,710
Thank you.

652
00:45:47,350 --> 00:45:48,610
You should sit back and relax.

653
00:45:48,640 --> 00:45:49,796
I’ll handle the rest.

654
00:45:49,820 --> 00:45:51,003
Okay.

655
00:45:51,025 --> 00:45:53,316
Our daughter is doing homework at the dining table.

656
00:46:03,690 --> 00:46:04,712
Hi, dear.

657
00:46:08,360 --> 00:46:11,890
You must be his favorite student.

658
00:46:12,200 --> 00:46:14,734
He never let anyone practice here before.

659
00:46:16,490 --> 00:46:17,570
I’ll be in your care.

660
00:46:17,880 --> 00:46:20,341
It’s nice having young people around some time.

661
00:46:20,378 --> 00:46:21,890
He gets to lighten up a bit.

662
00:46:22,280 --> 00:46:26,298
Otherwise, he’s just in his room brooding.

663
00:46:26,327 --> 00:46:27,327
Let me see.

664
00:46:28,760 --> 00:46:30,261
You’re good.

665
00:46:34,550 --> 00:46:35,738
Okay.

666
00:46:52,280 --> 00:46:53,280
Dream!

667
00:47:02,650 --> 00:47:03,650
Dream!

668
00:47:07,570 --> 00:47:08,363
Dream.

669
00:47:08,407 --> 00:47:10,360
Dream, slow down.

670
00:47:10,400 --> 00:47:12,320
- Don’t overdo it. You’re still injured.
- Dream!

671
00:47:13,290 --> 00:47:14,290
Dream!

672
00:47:49,240 --> 00:47:50,240
Get in the car.

673
00:47:56,320 --> 00:47:57,360
Stop being so stubborn.

674
00:48:18,407 --> 00:48:19,407
Let’s go home.

675
00:48:40,050 --> 00:48:42,661
MONTHS LATER

676
00:49:17,750 --> 00:49:18,923
Let’s go, Night.

677
00:49:20,680 --> 00:49:22,596
We have to get ready at the hospital.

678
00:49:25,840 --> 00:49:26,840
Yes.

679
00:50:00,470 --> 00:50:01,470
Are you ready?

680
00:50:03,370 --> 00:50:04,370
Yes.

681
00:50:12,501 --> 00:50:14,356
Nurse, scalpel.

682
00:50:32,320 --> 00:50:35,876
This is why I needed Ozone in the first place.

683
00:50:38,250 --> 00:50:41,185
Doc, if you don’t help us,

684
00:50:41,690 --> 00:50:43,016
get ready to see your secrets exposed.

685
00:50:43,040 --> 00:50:45,000
Who’d believe you?

686
00:50:45,025 --> 00:50:47,476
Why don’t we test it out with your family?

687
00:50:47,512 --> 00:50:49,774
I can march into your house and tell your wife right now

688
00:50:49,796 --> 00:50:52,632
that you killed the families of these two boys.

689
00:50:53,630 --> 00:50:55,214
There’s another way.

690
00:50:55,770 --> 00:50:58,465
If you die, at least you’ll die trying.
